              </label>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details open class="border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl bg-white shadow-sm">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer select-none px-5 py-4 font-semibold text-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl">6 · Output metrics; what to report</summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 space-y-4">
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Tick every metric to report. Each ticked metric gets its own section in the protocol output (Markdown + Word), with operational definition, formula, and unit. Mix-and-match freely; most descriptive AsPEN papers report 3-6 metrics.</p>
            {(["Occurrence", "Mortality", "Utilisation", "Adjustment", "Trends"] as const).map((group) => (
              <div>
                <p class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-600 font-bold">{group}</p>
                <div class="mt-1 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-1.5">
                  {OUTPUT_METRICS.filter((m) => m.group === group).map((m, i) => (
                    <label class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs border border-slate-200 rounded px-3 py-2 hover:bg-slate-50 cursor-pointer">
                      <input type="checkbox" name="metricsPick" value={m.id}
